  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Configure Roles For A Teamspace&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Pre-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul class=&quot;noindent&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The administrator has completed the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../extend.rup_abd/guidances/toolmentors/log_in_ram_D2EDCFF0.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_njZpIPSoEdqv1u-1M50ZsQ&quot;>Log In to RAM&lt;/a> scenario and been authenticated&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../extend.rup_abd/guidances/toolmentors/configure_teamspace_ram_A16F21DD.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Hz1b4PSvEdqv1u-1M50ZsQ&quot;>Configuring Communities using RAM&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;scenario has been completed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Objectives&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The list of permissions in&amp;nbsp;RAM are not configurable, meaning it is a finite set of capabilities which can be&#xD;
    configured. The set of permissions are associated with one or more roles.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;310&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/configure_roles_for_teamspace.png&quot; width=&quot;537&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Steps for Web UI&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click on Administration &amp;gt; Teamspace Administration &amp;gt; Roles&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click on the &lt;strong>Create a Role&lt;/strong> button&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Enter the name of the role and a description&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select one or more of the Role Entitlements to specify the capabilities the role will have in the repository&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select the roleâ€™s scope by entering constraints on the role, such as&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Asset Type&lt;/strong>: indicates that users with this role can work with assets of a given type&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Asset Classification&lt;/strong>: indicates that users with this role can work with assets classified&#xD;
                with a particular classification&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Asset Owner&lt;/strong>: indicates that users with this role can work with assets that are owned by a&#xD;
                specific owner&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Post-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        One or more roles are created and associated with a teamspace&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The&amp;nbsp;permissions for one or more roles have been specified&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>More Information&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please see the Rational Asset Manager related sections on developerWorks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
